%N A061009 a(n) = -2 + Sum_{j=1..n} (-(n-1)!) mod n.
%F A061009 a(n) = a(n-1) + A061007(n) = A061008(n) - 2. For n > 3, a(n) = pi(n) = A000720(n) where pi(n) is the number of primes less than or equal to n.
%e A061009 a(6)=3 since -2 + (-1 mod 1) + (-1 mod 2) + (-2 mod 3) + (-6 mod 4) + (-24 mod 5) + (-120 mod 6) = -2 + 0 + 1 + 1 + 2 + 1 + 0 = 3.
